{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel-B Model Context Protocol edge daemon, launched as a kernel init descendant (kind library so the build emits the thin ELF entry the kernel execve-s). It inherits the portal request/response eventfds (fd 3 and fd 4) and the portal region memfd (fd 5). At startup it maps the inherited region memfd fd 5 with MAP_SHARED to recover the shared portal region base and records it in g_portal_region_base (globals do not survive execve, so the base must be re-mapped here, not read from a parent global). It then reads its socket_path from the request, binds the pathname AF_UNIX stream socket, listens, and serves connections through the Channel-B accept loop, which submits every tools/call through the kernel portal instead of forking a shell. Additive Channel B edge alongside the Channel-A answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-socket; the Channel-A daemon is untouched.","module_name":"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-portal-region","package_name":"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-portal-region","function_definitions":{"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-portal-region":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment